  <prompt>
    Create a new `WorkspacePaneMenu` Fluent v9 Dropdown component and wire it into the WorkspacePane's
    `&lt;PaneHeader rightSlot=...&gt;`. Menu contains four sections separated by dividers per FR-12:
    (a) "Open" — list of currently open tabs, newest at top, each with `×` close (Home is non-closable);
    (b) "Home" — pinned non-closable LegalWorkspace entry; (c) "Switch Workspace" OptionGroup listing
    all layouts from `useWorkspaceLayouts` + "+ New Workspace" action; (d) "Edit current workspace"
    action. The "+ New Workspace" action launches `WorkspaceLayoutWizard` with the 6-template
    `templateFilter` prop added by task 033. Implements FR-12.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 + Fluent UI v9 component author. Bias toward composing the Fluent v9 `Menu` / `Dropdown` /
    `MenuList` primitives with dividers and OptionGroup; tokens only; keyboard-navigable; ARIA-labeled.
    Reuse `useWorkspaceLayouts` and `WorkspaceTabManager` — do not reinvent. Honor `WorkspaceLayoutWizard`'s
    `templateFilter` prop (added in task 033) when launching wizard for "+ New Workspace".
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePaneMenu.tsx` exports a
    `&lt;WorkspacePaneMenu /&gt;` component used as `&lt;PaneHeader rightSlot=&lt;WorkspacePaneMenu /&gt; /&gt;`
    inside `WorkspacePane.tsx`. The menu correctly renders the four required sections, dispatches
    correctly to `WorkspaceTabManager` on selection, and launches `WorkspaceLayoutWizard` with the
    6-template filter on "+ New Workspace". Keyboard-navigable; tokens-only styling.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-12 replaces the existing tab bar with a Fluent v9 Dropdown menu in the WorkspacePane header
      right-slot. The menu surfaces all four states: currently-open tabs (Open), the pinned Home tab,
      the workspace switcher (Switch Workspace, with "+ New Workspace" CTA), and an "Edit current
      workspace" action. The menu is the primary UX for moving between tabs and switching workspaces.
      Per FR-14, when "+ New Workspace" launches `WorkspaceLayoutWizard`, it passes `templateFilter`
      restricted to the SpaarkeAi 6-template subset (`2-col-equal`, `3-row-mixed`, `hero-2x2`,
      `sidebar-main`, `single-column`, `single-column-5`).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceTabManager.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/hooks/useWorkspaceLayouts.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/src/App.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/Shell/PageHeader.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">If `WorkspacePaneMenu` is context-agnostic, evaluate lifting to `@spaarke/ui-components` — but per OC-04 reuse first. Since the menu is SpaarkeAi-specific (depends on `WorkspaceTabManager` + workspace context), keep it solution-local in this task.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Use Fluent v9 tokens only. Use `Menu`, `MenuList`, `MenuItem`, `MenuDivider`, `MenuGroupHeader` from `@fluentui/react-components`. NO hex literals, NO `rgba(...)` literals, NO Fluent v8 components.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">Use `@fluentui/react-icons` (v9) for any icons — e.g., `DismissRegular` for the `×` close affordance, `AddRegular` for "+ New Workspace".</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Any new BFF calls (e.g., re-fetch layouts) go through `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`. NO `accessToken` props or state snapshots. Reuse `useWorkspaceLayouts` (which already obeys this).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-12 — Home is the only non-closable item; `×` close affordance MUST be hidden / disabled for the Home entry. FIFO eviction is enforced by `WorkspaceTabManager` (task 011 / FR-13).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-14 — when launching `WorkspaceLayoutWizard` from "+ New Workspace", pass `templateFilter={['2-col-equal','3-row-mixed','hero-2x2','sidebar-main','single-column','single-column-5']}` (the 6-template subset). Task 033 adds the prop; if 033 is not yet merged, surface that as a blocker.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-05 accessibility — the menu trigger has an `aria-label`; all menu items keyboard-navigable; screen-reader announces the active workspace and active tab.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
