      <file>docs/guides/WORKSPACE-AI-PREFILL-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read existing patterns">
      Read `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/Shell/PageHeader.tsx` to capture the existing
      workspace-switcher dropdown pattern. Read `WorkspaceTabManager.ts` to understand how tabs are
      added / closed / switched. Read `useWorkspaceLayouts.ts` to understand the layout-list contract.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Create WorkspacePaneMenu.tsx with Fluent v9 Dropdown">
      Create `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePaneMenu.tsx`. Use Fluent v9
      `Menu` / `MenuTrigger` / `MenuPopover` / `MenuList`. Trigger is an icon button (e.g., chevron)
      with an `aria-label`. Use `makeStyles` + `tokens.*` for any local styles.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Implement four sections with dividers">
      Within the `MenuList`, render four sections separated by `MenuDivider`:
      (a) "Open" — `MenuGroupHeader` + one `MenuItem` per currently-open non-Home tab, newest at top.
          Each item has the tab title on the left and a trailing `DismissRegular` icon button (the
          `×` close). Clicking the title selects the tab; clicking `×` removes it via
          `WorkspaceTabManager.removeTab(tabId)`.
      (b) "Home" — `MenuGroupHeader` + one `MenuItem` for Home, NO `×` (non-closable). Clicking
          selects the Home tab.
      (c) "Switch Workspace" — `MenuGroupHeader` + a list of `MenuItemRadio` / `OptionGroup` items
          from `useWorkspaceLayouts`, with the currently-active layout shown selected. Add a final
          `MenuItem` "+ New Workspace" with an `AddRegular` icon.
      (d) "Edit current workspace" — final `MenuItem` action that opens the existing edit flow
          (re-use whatever standalone LegalWorkspace uses; check `PageHeader.tsx`).
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Close × only on non-Home items">
      Confirm the `×` button is hidden/absent for the Home entry. Test: render menu with Home + 2
      tabs; verify only the 2 non-Home tabs show `×`.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Wire selection to WorkspaceTabManager">
      On `MenuItem` click in the "Open" section, call `WorkspaceTabManager.activateTab(tabId)`
      (or whatever the existing API is). On Home click, activate Home. Confirm the active tab
      switches in WorkspacePane content area.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire Switch Workspace to useWorkspaceLayouts">
      The "Switch Workspace" section is driven by `useWorkspaceLayouts()`. On selection of a layout,
      load it as the new active layout — call the existing API (whatever standalone LegalWorkspace
      does). Re-render Home tab with the new layout via the existing `WorkspaceShell` props.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire + New Workspace to WorkspaceLayoutWizard with templateFilter">
      "+ New Workspace" `MenuItem` click opens `WorkspaceLayoutWizard` with
      `templateFilter={['2-col-equal','3-row-mixed','hero-2x2','sidebar-main','single-column','single-column-5']}`
      (the 6-template subset per FR-14). Use the existing wizard's open/close mechanism (modal or
      navigation — match standalone LegalWorkspace).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Wire WorkspacePaneMenu into WorkspacePane rightSlot">
      Edit `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx`: change the
      `&lt;PaneHeader ... /&gt;` element to pass `rightSlot={&lt;WorkspacePaneMenu /&gt;}`. Confirm
      the menu trigger renders inside the pane header.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Add ARIA labels + keyboard nav check">
      Add `aria-label` on the menu trigger; ensure all `MenuItem` entries are keyboard-navigable.
      Tab through with keyboard only and confirm focus visibility on every item including `×`.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update TASK-INDEX and commit">
      Update `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: this task's status
      to ✅ completed. Commit changes per project conventions.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read existing PageHeader.tsx, WorkspaceTabManager.ts, useWorkspaceLayouts.ts, WorkspaceLayoutWizard App.tsx</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create WorkspacePaneMenu.tsx</tool>
